01:31.792 --> 01:34.292
Radio Moscow.
Director Andreyev. What is it?

01:37.667 --> 01:38.917
Seventeen minutes.

01:39.709 --> 01:42.626
Yes, of course I can ring back
in 17 minutes.

01:43.584 --> 01:44.584
Yeah.

01:45.626 --> 01:47.751
Mm-hm.
Yes, I'm writing it down.

01:48.917 --> 01:50.376
I can't get the...

01:50.501 --> 01:52.626
One, five...

01:54.126 --> 01:56.167
Sorry? Was that a nine, as in "fine"?

01:56.667 --> 01:59.001
Or... or another five as in, um...

01:59.584 --> 02:01.167
- "Hive."
- ..."hive"?

02:02.376 --> 02:04.542
Hello? Hello?

02:10.001 --> 02:12.167
- Hive?
- Who was it?

02:12.334 --> 02:14.417
The Secretariat
of the General Secretariat.

02:14.542 --> 02:17.417
Of the General Secretary.
The Secretary of the General...

02:17.542 --> 02:18.667
Stalin?

02:21.167 --> 02:22.876
Turn that down.

02:24.126 --> 02:25.376
Put that apple down.

02:25.459 --> 02:27.126
You're always eating bloody apples.

02:27.209 --> 02:29.251
I'm to call him back
in 17 minutes.

02:29.417 --> 02:31.185
Seventeen minutes from when
you picked up the phone

02:31.209 --> 02:33.167
or from when you put it down?

02:33.334 --> 02:37.251
Seventeen minutes from when I said
I'd call back in 17 minutes.

02:37.376 --> 02:39.376
- When was that?
- I don't know.

02:40.042 --> 02:41.167
Thirty seconds ago?

02:42.626 --> 02:44.084
- A minute?
- Well, which one?

02:44.209 --> 02:45.209
- A minute.
- A minute?

02:45.334 --> 02:46.417
A minute.

02:47.626 --> 02:48.834
- You sure?
- No.

02:54.084 --> 02:55.334
Well, well, well.

02:56.876 --> 02:59.584
Oh, I put Shteyman
on the list, the writer.

02:59.709 --> 03:03.167
- I know you like his work, but...
- No, leave him on.

03:03.292 --> 03:06.417
And, uh... Shteyman two, his wife?

03:06.542 --> 03:07.584
On.

03:08.167 --> 03:09.376
They're a couple, ain't they?

03:10.501 --> 03:12.310
We're talking about Stalingrad,
how cold it was,

03:12.334 --> 03:15.834
and we would do anything,
anything, to warm ourselves up.

03:16.001 --> 03:17.834
We'd throw live grenades
to each other.

03:17.917 --> 03:20.126
We'd pull the pin,
throw it to the prisoners.

03:20.209 --> 03:24.376
They'd be jumping around
like drunken whores. "Oh, oh, oh!"

03:24.459 --> 03:26.626
What was the grenade?

03:27.292 --> 03:28.834
- A grenade.
- Georgy.

03:28.917 --> 03:30.584
- A grenade... what do you...
- No no no.

03:30.667 --> 03:32.584
You're obstructing the story.
Let him tell it.

03:41.292 --> 03:43.792
<i>So, ten past, the call came in.</i>

03:44.251 --> 03:46.834
- Seventeen minutes...
- So call back 10:27?

03:47.959 --> 03:50.501
- Yeah.
- You don't seem confident.

03:50.626 --> 03:53.292
Well, I wasn't the one
on the phone.

03:53.376 --> 03:54.935
And it was definitely a nine,
wasn't it?

03:54.959 --> 03:57.417
- I wasn't the one on the phone.
- You keep saying that.

03:57.542 --> 04:01.834
- It's not helping.
- I wasn't, though. So...

04:01.959 --> 04:03.417
A grenade in his mouth!

04:04.917 --> 04:07.334
- Always cracks me up, this one.
- And then boom!

04:07.459 --> 04:08.667
I'll have these dispatched.

04:08.792 --> 04:10.876
That's how you turn a Prussian
into a bowl of soup.

04:11.667 --> 04:13.334
Oh, there he goes.

04:13.459 --> 04:15.209
Yes, we see your list, Beria.

04:18.791 --> 04:21.334
Shoot her before him,
but make sure he sees it.

04:21.459 --> 04:23.084
Oh, and this one... um...

04:24.042 --> 04:26.626
Kill him, take him to his church,
dump him in the pulpit.

04:27.667 --> 04:29.251
And I'll leave the rest
up to you.

04:30.459 --> 04:32.209
Let's go!

04:50.709 --> 04:53.626
First three names on list.
Top name, apartment 15. Go.

04:53.751 --> 04:54.917
Go, go.

05:16.459 --> 05:20.001
Come on. Where are you going?
Get round here. Get on the bus.

05:21.417 --> 05:24.376
Comrade, it's the greatest honour.

05:24.459 --> 05:26.001
He can't see me bow.

05:26.667 --> 05:28.542
- Comrade Director.
- Oh, shit.

05:32.917 --> 05:35.876
Five... nine.

05:40.251 --> 05:41.292
Hello.

05:42.042 --> 05:43.084
This is Stalin.

05:43.209 --> 05:44.792
Bravo!

05:44.917 --> 05:47.917
Sorry. It's really noisy.
I'm sorry about that.

05:48.042 --> 05:50.584
How are you?
How is it wherever you are?

05:50.709 --> 05:52.084
Sorry. Sorry again.

05:52.209 --> 05:54.126
<i>- Are you there?</i>
- Receiving you.

05:55.334 --> 05:57.417
I want a recording
of tonight's performance.

05:57.501 --> 05:58.959
I'll send someone to pick it up.

06:00.209 --> 06:01.834
I think you split
a couple of notes.

06:01.959 --> 06:03.376
You cheeky bugger. I did not.

06:03.501 --> 06:05.310
- How was it? Was it good?
- I thought wonderful.

06:05.334 --> 06:06.834
Was the concerto recorded?

06:08.751 --> 06:12.084
Was it recorded? Please say yes.

06:12.376 --> 06:16.292
- Erm... no. It went out live.
- Stay. Stay.

06:16.376 --> 06:19.584
Okay, nobody leave! Nobody leave!
Lock the doors! Lock those doors!

06:19.709 --> 06:21.435
If you wouldn't mind
just taking your seats again.

06:21.459 --> 06:22.542
That would be fantastic.

06:23.167 --> 06:24.352
Take your seats.
Take your fucking seats.

06:24.376 --> 06:28.084
Don't worry, nobody's
gonna get killed, I promise you.

06:28.209 --> 06:30.959
This is just
a musical emergency.

06:31.042 --> 06:32.292
Take your seats. That's it.

06:32.417 --> 06:33.959
Nobody be alarmed. It's fine.

06:34.042 --> 06:36.501
Sit down! Do not defy me!

06:36.667 --> 06:38.334
Sit your arses down!

06:40.751 --> 06:43.126
Top me up. Everybody drinks.

06:43.209 --> 06:45.501
As I was saying,
we had this 12-year-old scout.

06:45.626 --> 06:47.542
His whole family
was wiped out by the Krauts.

06:47.667 --> 06:50.626
But before that he taught us
this trick. He taught us this trick.

06:50.751 --> 06:53.376
He taught us this trick.
If you stick somebody's little finger

06:53.501 --> 06:56.667
in a glass of water
while they're sleeping,

06:56.792 --> 06:58.001
they wet themselves.

06:59.917 --> 07:00.959
Here, what next?

07:01.084 --> 07:02.501
You stick a bar of chocolate

07:02.584 --> 07:04.167
in their pocket,
they shit their pants?

07:07.917 --> 07:12.251
But it's biology, Chief.
We did it to Polnikov in Stalingrad.

07:12.417 --> 07:14.626
But, anyway,
"shit your pants", that's great.

07:14.751 --> 07:16.251
Whatever became of Polnikov?

07:20.209 --> 07:22.667
You wanna know
where fucking Polnikov is?

07:23.834 --> 07:24.917
You wanna go there?

07:26.001 --> 07:28.126
I love that grenade story.

07:29.417 --> 07:32.959
- Oh, is there one in your pocket?
- No, no, come on. No, not again!

07:33.042 --> 07:35.334
No, don't you...

07:35.459 --> 07:37.667
God damn it!

07:37.792 --> 07:40.167
Caught red-handed.

07:40.334 --> 07:42.376
Well, I would die for the Motherland!

07:45.209 --> 07:47.542
Whoa! Whoa! Whoa! Whoa!

08:05.251 --> 08:06.584
Wait a minute. Wait a minute.

08:07.709 --> 08:09.126
Take this, you bastards!

08:12.459 --> 08:13.667
All right, let's get going.

08:13.751 --> 08:16.584
Time for a cowboy movie.
Who's in my posse?

08:19.501 --> 08:22.542
Here we go. He rides out,
he gets shot off his horse.

08:24.667 --> 08:27.209
Adios.

08:28.792 --> 08:30.626
Thank you very much.
It's gonna be okay.

08:30.709 --> 08:31.834
Sit where you sat before.

08:32.376 --> 08:34.376
Right, what do you think?

08:34.626 --> 08:37.501
Well, half the audience have gone.
The acoustic will be very lively.

08:38.208 --> 08:40.667
Go and get some more people
in off the street.

08:40.792 --> 08:42.626
Fat ones, so we don't need as many.

08:42.833 --> 08:45.084
Really? How fat?

08:45.167 --> 08:48.501
I could get my wife.
She'd deaden the acoustic.

08:48.626 --> 08:51.376
Comrades...
Comrades, shut up!

08:52.001 --> 08:53.459
I have wonderful news.

08:53.584 --> 08:56.667
Comrade Stalin
loved tonight's concerto

08:56.792 --> 08:59.167
and would like
a recording of it right away,

08:59.334 --> 09:02.959
which we don't have, for reasons
that are myriad and complex and...

09:03.084 --> 09:09.334
But meanwhile the concerto
we just played will be played again.

09:09.459 --> 09:13.542
And this time we will record it
and we will applaud it.

09:16.001 --> 09:17.334
Yes. Yes.

09:32.209 --> 09:33.959
Brilliant. Okay.

09:35.667 --> 09:37.042
Excuse me.

09:37.667 --> 09:38.751
I won't do it.

09:40.084 --> 09:42.626
Come on, through here.
In you come.

09:46.001 --> 09:47.334
Sit down. Sit down.

09:48.459 --> 09:50.584
You, Joan of Arc,
do you want to get killed?

09:50.667 --> 09:52.834
Like my father got killed,
my brother? Like that?

09:53.667 --> 09:57.292
- But they would want you to live.
- I won't do it. You can't force me.

09:57.917 --> 10:00.185
- Can't we just get another pianist?
- That would be ridiculous.

10:00.209 --> 10:02.001
The sound would be
completely different.

10:02.126 --> 10:03.626
- Even Stalin could...
- Even?

10:03.959 --> 10:06.501
- I didn't mean...
- Even Stalin?

10:06.667 --> 10:08.126
I hope this office isn't bugged.

10:09.501 --> 10:11.685
Of course Comrade Stalin would
be able to tell the difference.

10:11.709 --> 10:15.001
He's a great man with a great ear.

10:15.126 --> 10:17.834
- Two great ears.
- Sharp. They're sharp.

10:17.959 --> 10:21.542
- The sharpest ears in the...
- In the Soviet Union.

10:21.667 --> 10:24.459
Maria Veniaminovna,
you have to play.

10:24.584 --> 10:26.501
I didn't...
I didn't mean what I said.

10:26.626 --> 10:27.792
So you said it, then?

10:28.751 --> 10:33.084
As God is my witness, I won't do it.
The Lord will see me through.

10:34.501 --> 10:35.751
10,000 roubles.

10:37.084 --> 10:38.292
20,000.

10:39.292 --> 10:41.292
Done. Let's go.

10:47.459 --> 10:48.459
Ohh!

10:48.542 --> 10:50.667
What the fuck?

10:50.792 --> 10:55.959
What fucking brainless fire-safety
fucking idiot put that there?

10:57.126 --> 10:59.626
Now we need a new conductor.
Let's go.

11:07.667 --> 11:09.001
Which one's your father in?

11:10.876 --> 11:12.917
Thank you. You've been very helpful.
Follow me.

11:14.834 --> 11:16.042
Open up!

11:16.876 --> 11:18.209
Let's get these on the bus.

11:18.292 --> 11:21.709
Keep it moving!
We've still got things to do!

11:21.834 --> 11:22.917
Come on, move!

11:36.584 --> 11:38.167
I love you. I love you.

11:38.292 --> 11:41.417
Now, you say whatever
you have to say to them. You say it.

11:41.834 --> 11:43.126
Oh, God.

11:44.042 --> 11:45.917
Hello. Hi.

11:46.376 --> 11:47.709
Deepest apologies, sir.

11:47.959 --> 11:50.334
Radio Moscow requests your
presence immediately, please.

11:50.459 --> 11:54.959
You're Moscow's finest and nearest
conductor, so... we must hurry.

12:02.417 --> 12:04.792
I rather enjoyed your reference
to Polnikov this evening.

12:04.876 --> 12:07.376
Stalin looked like he was
gonna split your head open.

12:07.501 --> 12:12.209
"What became of Polnikov and
Trotsky? I was a huge fan of his."

12:12.334 --> 12:13.876
"I miss the Tsar."

12:14.001 --> 12:17.001
I'm exhausted. I can't remember
who's alive and who isn't.

12:17.084 --> 12:19.542
Georgy, when you go home,
make sure your wife writes down

12:19.667 --> 12:21.501
everything you think
you said tonight.

12:21.626 --> 12:23.977
All right, this way in the morning
you know what you're dealing with.

12:24.001 --> 12:25.459
That's Khrushchev's Law.

12:25.542 --> 12:28.709
Good night, comrades. Long live
the Communist Party of Lenin-Stalin.

12:29.251 --> 12:31.126
Long live John Wayne
and John Ford.

12:33.417 --> 12:35.167
Goodbye, Molotov, old friend.

12:35.292 --> 12:36.417
Goodbye forever.

12:38.209 --> 12:39.584
Yeah. On the list.

12:40.459 --> 12:41.751
It would be simpler and cheaper

12:41.834 --> 12:43.459
if they just drove
straight into a river.

12:45.084 --> 12:46.251
Sweet dreams.

12:48.792 --> 12:50.126
Good night.

12:54.251 --> 12:55.334
Night.

13:04.667 --> 13:05.959
People in off the streets.

13:06.042 --> 13:07.167
Just this way.

13:12.334 --> 13:15.417
I don't think any of these people
have ever heard of Mozart.

13:40.126 --> 13:41.584
<i>I made a joke about the farmers.</i>

13:41.917 --> 13:44.376
- Did Stalin laugh?
- Yeah.

13:46.417 --> 13:48.251
I made a joke about the navy.

13:48.459 --> 13:50.876
- No laugh.
- No more navy jokes.

13:51.417 --> 13:52.459
Good evening.

13:52.584 --> 13:54.126
Get this lot checked in.

13:54.417 --> 13:55.501
Good. Nice.

13:55.584 --> 13:57.417
Long live Stalin!

14:01.501 --> 14:03.459
Long live Stalin!

14:27.626 --> 14:29.792
- Shouldn't we check it?
- No time.

14:31.209 --> 14:34.084
If it's not okay, then Stalin's men
will chop you into dog meat.

14:34.167 --> 14:35.167
Thank you.

14:35.626 --> 14:38.834
Move, move, move, move, move.
Excuse me. Thank you.

14:38.917 --> 14:40.626
I have it. I have it.

14:43.459 --> 14:48.792
I have the recording. I just had to
get a new sleeve, a white one.

14:48.876 --> 14:50.459
The delay has been logged.

14:50.584 --> 14:53.292
I wish to convey a special
message from my heart.

14:53.376 --> 14:56.251
I wish to convey this recording
to Comrade Stalin.

14:56.376 --> 14:58.126
I want Comrade Stalin to know

14:58.209 --> 15:00.542
the full intensity
of my feelings for him.

15:01.126 --> 15:02.834
No, this is unauthorised narcissism.

15:02.917 --> 15:04.042
No.

15:05.459 --> 15:09.126
The item is now in my possession...
after a significant delay.

15:09.209 --> 15:10.459
Note the time.

15:39.501 --> 15:41.709
What took you so long?
You fucking walk here?

16:05.501 --> 16:07.376
<i>Josef Vissarionovich Stalin,</i>

16:07.459 --> 16:10.292
<i>you have betrayed our nation
and destroyed its people.</i>

16:10.876 --> 16:14.084
<i>I pray for your end,
and ask the Lord to forgive you.</i>

16:14.209 --> 16:15.542
<i>Tyrant.</i>

16:22.126 --> 16:25.209
Oh, fuck. Fuck...

16:33.834 --> 16:35.209
Should we investigate?

16:35.584 --> 16:38.626
Should you shut the fuck up
before you get us both killed?

16:49.834 --> 16:51.126
Good morning.

16:54.709 --> 16:55.834
Well?

16:59.626 --> 17:01.251
Comrade Stalin?

17:02.251 --> 17:03.917
Comrade Stalin?

17:07.334 --> 17:08.709
I just need some names.

17:09.334 --> 17:12.251
Each name you give me
is one less bit of you I'll cut off.

17:12.376 --> 17:14.376
Enter.

17:16.251 --> 17:20.251
Sorry to interrupt, Comrade Minister.
It's Comrade Stalin.

17:21.791 --> 17:24.459
Oh, don't worry about him.
Those ears are full of blood anyway.

17:25.709 --> 17:27.376
Comrade Stalin is very ill.

17:28.084 --> 17:29.209
Very ill?

17:29.959 --> 17:31.001
Yes.

17:32.334 --> 17:33.459
Uh-huh.

17:34.417 --> 17:36.501
- You, carry on.
- Of course.

17:38.292 --> 17:41.251
Tell them Beria is on his way.

17:41.959 --> 17:46.626
They are to touch nothing,
call no-one. Understood?

17:47.376 --> 17:49.376
Tell me you understand
my instructions.

17:49.459 --> 17:51.542
I understand your instructions.

17:51.667 --> 17:53.001
Good.

17:53.126 --> 17:55.959
Shh, shh.

17:56.542 --> 17:58.042
What's your name, Lieutenant?

17:59.626 --> 18:01.042
S-Slimonov, sir.

18:01.167 --> 18:02.584
S-Slimonov?

18:03.792 --> 18:05.584
Be here when I g-get back.

18:07.459 --> 18:09.459
Long live Stalin!

18:13.542 --> 18:16.501
- Abramovsky still holding out?
- Yeah. He's close, though.

18:16.751 --> 18:18.376
He was close yesterday.

18:18.501 --> 18:19.792
Long live Stalin!

18:19.876 --> 18:21.501
Have his wife move into the next cell

18:21.584 --> 18:23.167
and start working
on her until he talks.

18:23.292 --> 18:24.667
Make it noisy.

18:24.792 --> 18:28.001
Shame. Mrs Abramovsky's been
most cooperative so far.

18:29.292 --> 18:32.126
Some women will do anything
to get their husbands released.

18:32.251 --> 18:34.334
Yeah, and she did everything.

18:34.459 --> 18:37.417
I thank the Union for bringing me
so many devoted wives

18:37.501 --> 18:39.459
who fuck like sewing machines.

18:39.876 --> 18:41.042
Glasses.

18:43.626 --> 18:45.376
To his dacha. Urgently.

18:53.001 --> 18:55.251
Tanks, farmers, navy,

18:55.376 --> 18:56.792
grenade: funny.

18:56.917 --> 18:59.876
Beria, tomato, pocket: funny. Horse...

19:00.001 --> 19:01.792
- Funny?
- ...slippers: question mark.

19:01.876 --> 19:04.501
- Farmers, horse again, navy...
- There were no whores.

19:04.876 --> 19:08.209
What are you writing?
Oh, "horse". Is this in code?

19:08.334 --> 19:10.792
This is your drunken nonsense,
not mine. Don't blame my notes.

19:10.917 --> 19:13.459
"Molotov C-H-H-H..."

19:13.584 --> 19:15.167
Was I stuttering? What is that?

19:15.292 --> 19:16.959
Molotov...

19:18.209 --> 19:20.792
Oh. It's Molotov...

19:22.167 --> 19:24.167
- He's on the list.
- Poor Molotov.

19:24.792 --> 19:26.501
First his wife, now him.

19:27.167 --> 19:29.626
Georgy is off in a hurry somewhere.

19:30.126 --> 19:31.251
Something's happening.

19:33.001 --> 19:34.126
Hello?

19:34.584 --> 19:35.626
What?

19:35.709 --> 19:36.959
Get my trousers.

19:37.167 --> 19:39.334
Just get my... No, not you.

19:39.459 --> 19:41.292
Who's there? Is Beria there?

19:41.417 --> 19:42.876
Never mind. I'll be right there.

19:43.584 --> 19:45.518
Your trousers. Your trousers.
Here are your trousers.

19:45.542 --> 19:47.209
- Okay, okay.
- Let me take your pyjamas.

19:47.751 --> 19:50.959
No, there's no time. Get my
shoes, please, Nina, my shoes.

19:51.042 --> 19:52.876
- Your shirt.
- Send me a shirt and tie.

20:11.376 --> 20:12.834
Were you on duty
when he was found?

20:12.959 --> 20:15.501
- Yes, sir.
- No-one is to come in. Understood?

20:15.626 --> 20:17.001
Yes, sir.

20:17.084 --> 20:18.501
Remain at your stations.

20:22.667 --> 20:23.917
Oh, God.

20:28.042 --> 20:30.376
They told me
not to get a doctor.

20:30.501 --> 20:31.959
You did well, Matryona Petrovna.

20:32.084 --> 20:33.959
The Central Committee
will handle things now.

20:34.209 --> 20:36.876
- So they'll get a doctor?
- There are procedures in place.

20:38.167 --> 20:40.209
- So you'll get a doctor?
- I am the doctor.

20:41.334 --> 20:42.917
I'll see to everything. Come on.

20:46.209 --> 20:47.459
Go on. He'll be fine.

20:51.501 --> 20:53.584
Smells like a Baku pisshouse in here.

20:55.626 --> 20:56.667
Greetings, by the way.

21:01.001 --> 21:02.126
Oh, shit.

21:07.542 --> 21:08.667
Uh-huh.

21:27.209 --> 21:29.042
Oh, come on. Fuck!

21:48.959 --> 21:51.709
Khrustalyov! Khrustalyov!

21:55.834 --> 21:57.542
- Take the papers.
- Let them go.

21:57.709 --> 21:59.685
Take the papers or I'll cut
your eyes out one at a time

21:59.709 --> 22:00.917
so you can watch it happening!

22:01.042 --> 22:02.376
- Drop it.
- Take them!

22:27.209 --> 22:28.626
Come in.

22:33.834 --> 22:35.209
Oh, my God.

22:39.959 --> 22:43.042
Is this...
I'm guessing that this is...

22:43.209 --> 22:45.792
Yeah, he's feeling unwell, clearly.

