34:05.042 --> 34:07.522
Are they going to sing for us?
Why are they standing in a line?

34:08.333 --> 34:09.417
Let's have it.

34:17.251 --> 34:20.917
Following a group assessment
of Comrade Stalin,

34:21.001 --> 34:24.417
we've arrived
at the unanimous conclusion,

34:24.542 --> 34:26.167
based on a collective finding...

34:26.251 --> 34:27.708
Please put him out of his misery.

34:28.626 --> 34:31.542
Comrade Stalin has had
a cerebral haemorrhage.

34:31.626 --> 34:33.626
The right side of his body
is paralysed.

34:33.708 --> 34:34.792
Oh, God.

34:36.583 --> 34:38.208
What is the chance of recovery?

34:38.333 --> 34:39.751
It is hard to say.

34:42.251 --> 34:46.751
Relax. I'm not gonna kiss you.
Will he recover, yes or no?

34:51.292 --> 34:52.292
No.

34:52.376 --> 34:53.751
- No?
- No.

34:55.958 --> 34:57.001
It's over.

34:57.917 --> 34:59.334
It's over!

34:59.417 --> 35:02.709
I want a second opinion.
I don't trust these creatures to...

35:02.876 --> 35:05.542
- I mean, how old are you?
- I'm 29.

35:05.626 --> 35:07.376
That's a lie. How old are you?

35:07.459 --> 35:08.626
You look dead.

35:09.584 --> 35:11.959
I know people in Stalingrad.
I know people in Moscow.

35:12.084 --> 35:16.417
No, no, no. We have all the doctors.
There is no other opinion.

35:16.542 --> 35:18.834
- Oh, God.
- And so it begins.

35:18.917 --> 35:19.917
Oh, God!

35:20.001 --> 35:22.667
I cry for Stalin.
I cry for all the people.

35:22.751 --> 35:25.001
- I cry for the...
- Courage.

35:26.042 --> 35:28.792
Courage, little bird.
We're here for you.

35:31.334 --> 35:33.209
Most of all, we cry for you,

35:33.292 --> 35:35.626
