Trophy hunting, comrade?

36:44.959 --> 36:48.209
Oh, Svetlana. No, no. I was...

36:48.334 --> 36:51.459
We were just about to make a toast
to your father's health

36:51.584 --> 36:55.876
and I know he kept
some fine vodka here somewhere.

36:56.084 --> 36:58.542
Well, better you find it
than my brother.

36:58.626 --> 37:00.542
Ah, yes. Vasily.

37:01.251 --> 37:03.167
I got a hold of him
and he's on his way.

37:04.251 --> 37:05.959
- Oh...
- Svetlana, I wanted to...

37:06.042 --> 37:09.959
There was one day when my brother
just rode a pig through here.

37:10.667 --> 37:13.542
- That must have been messy.
- It was terribly messy.

37:13.626 --> 37:15.917
And my father was so cross.

37:16.001 --> 37:18.334
Papa just chased him
around the room in a circle.

37:18.417 --> 37:20.667
Right here around this sofa,
just there, look.

37:20.751 --> 37:25.251
Yes, I wanted to let you know
that no matter what happens,

37:25.334 --> 37:30.084
I will never ever let any harm
come to you or your brother.

37:30.167 --> 37:33.042
- Who said anything about harm?
- No, that's what I'm saying.

37:33.126 --> 37:34.751
You know somebody
wants to harm us?

37:34.876 --> 37:36.596
- Tell me. I demand to know.
- If someone...

37:36.667 --> 37:38.501
No. I should not have used
the word "harm".

37:38.584 --> 37:40.544
Yes. But you keep mentioning
the word "harm". Why?

37:41.209 --> 37:47.209
If anyone tries to... you,
they'll have to get through me first.

37:52.417 --> 37:53.959
My father's going to die.

37:54.042 --> 37:56.001
I'm going to have you
to look after me.

37:56.792 --> 37:59.084
I mean, I may as well
just shoot myself like Mother.

37:59.917 --> 38:03.501
- Svetlana, we need to be strong.
- Who would put a lamp on a chair?

38:07.917 --> 38:11.417
We need to be strong
and never afraid.

38:11.501 --> 38:14.959
- I wasn't afraid. Now I am afraid.
- Don't be, because if any harm...

38:15.042 --> 38:16.209
God, I actually...

38:16.292 --> 38:17.518
can't believe you said that again.

38:17.542 --> 38:19.209
Quick! The boss is back!

38:19.292 --> 38:20.709
- Ohh!
- Come on!

38:23.376 --> 38:25.834
- Papa!
- A miracle.

38:26.001 --> 38:27.251
Stalin is invincible.

38:27.417 --> 38:29.959
The boss has shipped death
back to the salt mine.

38:30.084 --> 38:32.334
What's happening?
This is impossible...

38:34.084 --> 38:36.501
and... and... and wonderful.

38:38.001 --> 38:40.126
- He's pointing...
- What is it, Chief?

38:40.376 --> 38:43.167
Maybe he's appointing his successor.

38:43.251 --> 38:44.292
Do you think?

38:46.167 --> 38:47.376
- No.
- Maybe not.

38:48.667 --> 38:50.018
- What's he...
- It's the painting.

38:50.042 --> 38:52.834
- He's pointing at the painting.
- Hold on. You know what he's saying?

38:52.917 --> 38:55.001
He is saying, "I am the lamb."

38:55.417 --> 38:56.459
Huh?

38:56.542 --> 39:00.459
"I am the lamb and you, you,
my children, have given me life."

39:00.584 --> 39:01.626
Yes!

39:02.334 --> 39:07.709
Or the lamb is the people
and the milk is socialism.

39:07.792 --> 39:08.917
Maybe he's the milk.

39:09.417 --> 39:10.876
Maybe you're the tit.

39:10.959 --> 39:14.251
- Maybe he just wants a drink.
- A drink of milk.

39:14.917 --> 39:16.917
- Possible.
- Milk here! Immediately!

39:17.042 --> 39:20.667
- Not milk. Water. Water.
- And not in a horn. In a glass.

39:22.417 --> 39:23.667
So, Top Boy.

39:23.792 --> 39:26.292
You had your hair
fucking embalmed or something?

39:27.376 --> 39:28.751
I owe it to him and the people.

39:29.917 --> 39:32.001
- There's going to be photos.
- Oh, right.

39:33.459 --> 39:35.917
You're a hero, Comrade Lukomsky.

39:36.001 --> 39:39.917
This sometimes happens and I...

39:40.751 --> 39:43.167
I'm incredibly pleased.

39:46.792 --> 39:48.042
I won't forget it.

39:58.584 --> 39:59.584
Comrade.

40:00.917 --> 40:03.667
We've remained at our post
as you ordered.

40:04.334 --> 40:06.959
Might we respectfully
stand down from our position?

40:07.042 --> 40:08.084
Beria...

40:09.459 --> 40:10.584
...he's dead.

40:34.501 --> 40:36.667
- Oh, Jesus!
- Fuck my boots!

40:36.751 --> 40:38.459
Oh, my God.

40:38.542 --> 40:40.876
I'm sorry, boss.
I wish I could take it for you.

40:41.001 --> 40:44.751
Thick skull, you know. It's
an incredibly strong, hard skull.

40:44.834 --> 40:46.001
Shut up.

40:46.084 --> 40:47.667
We need to think about the Presidium.

40:47.792 --> 40:50.251
Yes, succession. We need to...

40:51.167 --> 40:53.917
Oh, fuck. That's his...

40:56.376 --> 40:57.709
Who organised the Wurlitzer?

40:57.792 --> 41:00.584
- It's a respirator.
- Did you use it?

41:00.709 --> 41:03.501
- No. It's American.
- It's what?

41:03.584 --> 41:05.542
- It's from his hospital.
- It was his idea.

41:05.667 --> 41:08.876
Let's just pretend these last
six sentences never happened.

41:08.959 --> 41:10.852
Because if they ever find out
that we brought in...

41:10.876 --> 41:13.667
What are you doing to my father,
you jackals? Murderers!

41:13.792 --> 41:16.084
- You'll kill him!
- Vasily, your father is dead.

41:16.209 --> 41:19.334
You're dividing the spoils.
Leave his brain alone!

41:19.417 --> 41:20.876
- How old are you?
- I'm old.

41:20.959 --> 41:23.126
You're not old!
You're not even a person!

41:23.251 --> 41:26.167
You're a testicle!
You're made mostly of hair!

41:26.251 --> 41:28.042
- Vasily...
- Here's your fucking harvest.

41:28.126 --> 41:29.626
Here it is.

41:29.709 --> 41:31.834
Leave the man alone! I will not...

41:32.876 --> 41:34.876
No! Don't let him shoot!

41:34.959 --> 41:37.167
- Just get the gun off him.
- Vasily!

41:37.251 --> 41:39.584
- Let her through.
- Remember what Papa said.

41:39.709 --> 41:41.949
They have a machine
filling his brain with American lies.

41:42.001 --> 41:43.459
"Wade gently through the river

41:43.542 --> 41:45.667
because there are snakes
and crocodiles."

41:45.751 --> 41:48.542
It's okay, Vasily.
Everything's gonna be fine.

41:48.626 --> 41:51.501
- This is not exactly fine, is it?
- No, well, not exactly fine.

41:51.626 --> 41:53.143
My father's lying there
with his head open.

41:53.167 --> 41:55.917
Yes, your father is dead.
Your brother is shooting a gun.

41:56.001 --> 41:57.251
It's not fine. You're right.

41:57.376 --> 41:58.584
Come on. There we go.

41:59.751 --> 42:02.751
You have all made
a deadly mistake.

42:07.376 --> 42:09.959
- Excuse me.
- That's right. Off you go, kitten.

42:31.959 --> 42:33.542
Oh, come on.

42:36.792 --> 42:39.501
- Just keep the gun away from him.
- I've got loads, anyway.

42:39.626 --> 42:41.126
Have you forgotten
how to salute?

42:41.209 --> 42:43.376
- No, sir.
- Then salute me.

42:45.334 --> 42:47.292
Now, let that be a warning.

42:48.084 --> 42:50.876
"Be strong," I hear my father say.

42:51.126 --> 42:52.167
Come on, chop, chop.

42:52.251 --> 42:53.459
Beria's picked you out.

42:54.917 --> 42:56.001
Just do as he says.

42:56.126 --> 43:00.126
- My car is right this way.
- No, no. She'll be happier with us.

43:00.209 --> 43:02.209
Okay, but we need to go. Let's go.

43:03.459 --> 43:05.126
- See you in Moscow.
- See you.

43:08.251 --> 43:09.584
Ah, nice.

43:17.834 --> 43:21.084
We need to go through first!
No, let us go first!

43:36.542 --> 43:37.584
Go, go, go!

43:45.001 --> 43:46.042
Go!

43:48.334 --> 43:50.209
Shit.
What, are we last now? Come on.

44:12.959 --> 44:15.292
Comrades, we share your grief.

44:15.376 --> 44:18.209
You will assemble outside
for further instructions.

44:18.292 --> 44:21.251
All staff into the transport.
Yes, that's it, hurry up.

44:21.334 --> 44:23.626
Come on, get a move on.
In the transports, please.

44:23.709 --> 44:26.959
Where the fuck
did she come from? Get her out!

44:27.084 --> 44:28.709
Gently with that, will you?
Hurry up.

44:30.292 --> 44:32.292
That's it, everything out.

44:38.334 --> 44:40.626
Lookalikes.
I think their contract's up.

44:40.834 --> 44:41.834
This way.

44:43.959 --> 44:47.876
- You, come with me.
- But I don't understand.

44:49.501 --> 44:51.209
Come on. Just this way.

44:51.292 --> 44:52.292
You can stand down.

44:52.834 --> 44:53.834
Food in the kitchen.

45:01.667 --> 45:02.876
Halt!

45:03.042 --> 45:04.667
Move them out!

45:10.126 --> 45:11.917
Last one! Move it out!

45:29.501 --> 45:30.584
<i>Hello again.</i>

45:32.042 --> 45:33.042
There you are.

45:35.709 --> 45:36.876
You're very quiet.

45:41.001 --> 45:43.709
See the little birch in the meadow.

45:44.917 --> 45:48.126
See the leaves dancing
when the wind blows.

45:50.042 --> 45:51.084
No?

45:51.792 --> 45:55.751
Well, come on, your voice was once
so beautiful, Polina Molotova.

45:58.084 --> 46:00.292
Oh, yes, sorry, meant to say.

46:01.501 --> 46:02.709
Stalin's dead.

46:04.167 --> 46:07.251
No. The Stalin?

46:08.584 --> 46:10.209
Our Stalin?

46:11.292 --> 46:13.834
Yeah, your Stalin.

46:15.501 --> 46:16.667
The one who put you here.

46:18.292 --> 46:19.292
Come on.

46:20.417 --> 46:23.751
Let's smarten you up
for Comrade Molotov.

46:24.126 --> 46:27.001
Good girl. Come on.

46:28.459 --> 46:32.251
Oh, sorry, darling. Work.
I'll make it up to you.

46:32.709 --> 46:35.251
Fetch the mattress
and have her washed.

46:35.334 --> 46:36.334
Okay.

46:36.876 --> 46:38.459
Right, get in there. Go on.

46:39.292 --> 46:40.917
Right, with me. Come on.

46:41.001 --> 46:44.501
All right, jug, rug, flowers.
Right, grab that.

46:46.292 --> 46:48.501
- S-Slimonov, isn't it?
- Yes, sir.

46:48.584 --> 46:50.709
See you I-later, S-Slimonov.

46:51.501 --> 46:52.501
Come on.

46:56.167 --> 46:59.167
Bought you a lovely new dress,
a nice dress.

47:22.917 --> 47:24.459
Oh, God.

47:27.334 --> 47:31.167
Christ. You look like you're about
to be bulldozed into a lime pit.

47:31.292 --> 47:32.501
Need your toilet.

47:36.917 --> 47:39.126
Do you want me to hold back your hair?

47:39.251 --> 47:41.126
Polina always used to do that for me.

47:41.584 --> 47:42.917
Oh, no. Nothing's coming up.

47:43.709 --> 47:45.709
Futile gesture.

47:45.792 --> 47:50.751
Listen, I wanted to invite you
to tomorrow's Committee meeting.

47:50.959 --> 47:51.959
Meeting?

47:53.376 --> 47:55.709
What meeting?
Why didn't I know about a meeting?

48:02.792 --> 48:05.584
Stalin and Beria put you on a list.

48:07.959 --> 48:09.001
Stalin?

48:11.209 --> 48:14.626
Oh, I must have wronged him so badly.
What did I do?

48:14.792 --> 48:18.792
No, nothing. Don't you see?
Beria, he wants you out.

48:19.459 --> 48:21.219
Now, I've been talking
with Comrade Bulganin.

48:21.292 --> 48:22.292
No. No.

48:22.376 --> 48:23.893
I think he's right.
We can outvote them.

48:23.917 --> 48:26.376
No, no. This is factionalism.
Stalin didn't like factionalism.

48:26.459 --> 48:28.084
Oh, Stalin is dead!

48:29.084 --> 48:32.792
I've seen inside of him.
For fuck's sake, we have to act.

48:32.876 --> 48:35.209
I can't believe he's gone.

48:36.709 --> 48:38.417
Ohh...

48:44.501 --> 48:46.876
You have to wait for it to fill up.

48:48.167 --> 48:50.167
Fucking apartments.

48:51.709 --> 48:52.792
Listen to me.

48:53.542 --> 48:55.876
Beria had Polina killed.

48:56.959 --> 48:59.209
Now, surely you must have wanted to...

48:59.292 --> 49:01.959
Act against the party? Me?

49:02.084 --> 49:03.584
- No?
- No, never.

49:03.667 --> 49:04.792
- Really?
- No.

49:04.876 --> 49:06.626
- Not once?
- Not once.

49:06.709 --> 49:09.501
Hello? Anyone home?

49:09.584 --> 49:11.917
- What are you doing here?
- What are <i>you</i> doing here?

49:12.834 --> 49:14.376
We were just chatting.

49:14.459 --> 49:16.209
About Polina.

49:17.126 --> 49:20.251
- Well, well, would you believe it?
- Treacherous sow.

49:21.542 --> 49:24.417
Or a wronged woman who was framed.

49:24.542 --> 49:26.167
No, no. She was a criminal.

49:26.792 --> 49:27.834
I'm glad she's dead.

49:28.417 --> 49:31.376
Right, because,
well, she betrayed the party.

49:31.459 --> 49:34.084
- She plotted against Stalin.
- No, Nicky. False narrative.

49:34.167 --> 49:36.792
- No, no, she was a parasite.
- She <i>was</i> a parasite.

49:36.917 --> 49:41.501
She betrayed all of us, and, in fact,
the evidence was flimsy.

49:41.626 --> 49:44.584
There were no witnesses.
And look. Polina's back.

49:44.667 --> 49:46.459
Is it really you?

49:46.876 --> 49:51.042
Oh, my Polina.
Oh, I can't believe it.

49:51.126 --> 49:52.917
Oh, look, everyone, look.

49:53.001 --> 49:56.417
- My little Polinka's back.
- I am back.

49:56.542 --> 49:59.584
I kept her safe for you, Vyacheslav.

49:59.667 --> 50:01.917
And I kept him safe for you, Polina.

50:02.042 --> 50:04.334
- I've got so much to tell you.
- Good.

50:04.417 --> 50:06.376
- I've bought a dog...
- Oh?

50:06.459 --> 50:08.292
So many changes to come.

50:09.834 --> 50:11.709
And you're gonna like
some of them, Nicky.

50:15.209 --> 50:16.667
It's great to have you back.

50:28.792 --> 50:30.126
Hello, my sweet.

50:39.251 --> 50:40.376
You're the parents?

50:43.001 --> 50:45.501
Thank you. You should go now.

50:50.417 --> 50:51.751
<i>We ready?</i>

50:52.834 --> 50:54.001
<i>Good.</i>

50:56.542 --> 50:58.667
Now, please don't go
until I say, okay?

51:00.751 --> 51:01.792
Did you hear me?

51:08.376 --> 51:09.501
Okay.

51:11.834 --> 51:13.834
Yes? It's good?

51:14.834 --> 51:16.876
I'd like to try one
with a faraway look.

51:19.084 --> 51:20.126
Comrade,

51:20.209 --> 51:23.501
I've scheduled some telephone calls
later with various members of the...

51:23.667 --> 51:25.417
I can't hear you.
Can you say that again?

51:25.542 --> 51:28.709
I'm sorry. I've scheduled
some telephone calls later with...

51:28.792 --> 51:30.959
- Then tell me later.
- Of course.

51:31.042 --> 51:33.917
Mr Karloff, what an honour.
Love your work.

51:34.542 --> 51:37.876
Thinking of doing anything in colour?

51:38.209 --> 51:40.001
I need to talk to you about something.

51:40.126 --> 51:41.584
Would you please excuse me?

51:43.959 --> 51:45.167
I'll be right back.

51:50.417 --> 51:53.334
Don't you ever... ever...

51:54.459 --> 51:56.042
humiliate me again in front of...

51:56.834 --> 51:59.709
I am the General Secretary
of the Soviet Union.

51:59.792 --> 52:01.501
Apologies. A line has been crossed.

52:01.584 --> 52:04.167
It is my duty to look good
for the people.

52:04.251 --> 52:06.584
- Of course.
- Ah, comrade, apologies.

52:06.667 --> 52:09.084
I'm not gonna do the seating plan.
Give it to Blavatsky.

52:09.167 --> 52:12.042
- He's expert at sitting on his arse.
- Of course. Thank you.

52:12.126 --> 52:13.792
- The Committee meeting...
- Oh, yes, yes.

52:13.917 --> 52:18.501
Um, item one:
these lists and these arrests.

52:19.167 --> 52:22.001
I think we...
Should we take that down just a gear?

52:22.084 --> 52:23.459
Or hold off altogether?

52:25.459 --> 52:27.626
- Freeze them?
- Freeze, yes.

52:27.709 --> 52:29.834
Excellent thought.
Yes, we could freeze arrests.

52:29.917 --> 52:32.042
We could even release
some low-level prisoners.

52:32.167 --> 52:35.876
Fuck me. I mean... I mean, yes.

52:35.959 --> 52:37.626
But what would the old man...

52:37.751 --> 52:42.376
Oh, Stalin... Stalin destroyed
the status quo and he built a new one.

52:42.459 --> 52:45.084
The changes he made
were both radical and popular.

52:45.167 --> 52:47.209
- Liberalisation would be radical.
- Popular.

52:47.334 --> 52:49.042
- Radical.
- And popular.

52:49.126 --> 52:51.959
I will deal with whatever horseshit

52:52.042 --> 52:53.376
you have presently.

52:53.459 --> 52:55.959
- Actually, I'd like you to see this.
- Come on through.

52:56.667 --> 53:00.667
You remember that famous photo
of Stalin and the little girl?

53:00.751 --> 53:01.792
Yes.

53:01.876 --> 53:05.417
Well, I was thinking
a photo of, you and the girl.

53:05.501 --> 53:06.792
Continuity.

53:07.251 --> 53:10.459
And this way we're showing Stalin's
humanity moving forward, right?

53:10.542 --> 53:11.667
Yeah.

53:12.626 --> 53:14.917
I'm sorry about all that.
Find the girl.

53:15.001 --> 53:16.751
- We should head to the Committee.
- We are.

53:21.459 --> 53:23.917
So I'll outline the releases
under Article 31.

53:24.001 --> 53:25.709
- Yes, please.
- Okay.

53:26.501 --> 53:30.292
Please, understand that this
is not some cynical ploy.

53:30.376 --> 53:33.376
I mean, these reforms
are correct reforms.

53:33.459 --> 53:34.501
Totally understood.

53:37.334 --> 53:38.584
Are you wearing a corset?

53:42.084 --> 53:44.834
It's a girdle. I have a bad back.

53:46.167 --> 53:48.917
It's functional. It's not cosmetic.

53:49.001 --> 53:50.126
You wear it well.

53:52.042 --> 53:54.709
Let's make this
a test of your discretion, shall we?

53:54.792 --> 53:56.376
Of course. Of course.

54:05.334 --> 54:07.435
- So, in accordance...
- I call this meeting to order.

54:07.459 --> 54:08.792
My apologies.

54:09.542 --> 54:13.584
So, in accordance with his will,
I propose Comrade Malenkov

54:13.667 --> 54:15.393
be named Chairman
of the Council of Ministers

54:15.417 --> 54:17.417
and General Secretary of the Party.

54:17.834 --> 54:20.167
And I propose Comrade Beria

54:20.251 --> 54:23.042
for First Vice-Chairman,
Council of Ministers.

54:23.126 --> 54:25.501
So, let's take a vote.
Those in favour?

54:25.584 --> 54:27.292
Those are two separate proposals.

54:27.376 --> 54:30.042
I suggest we vote one at a time.
Those in favour?

54:30.209 --> 54:32.667
I'm unsure of what's being proposed.

54:32.751 --> 54:34.834
I just said what was being proposed.
I just said it.

54:34.959 --> 54:36.834
And you're being obstructionist.

54:36.917 --> 54:39.501
Comrade Beria is busy
combining his role

54:39.584 --> 54:41.709
as Minister for both
Interior and Security.

54:41.834 --> 54:43.876
Wouldn't it be kinder if someone else

54:43.959 --> 54:45.626
carried the happy burden
of Vice-Chairman?

54:45.709 --> 54:47.389
I thank Comrade Khrushchev
for his concern,

54:47.501 --> 54:50.167
but I'm perfectly capable
of doing two things at once.

54:50.251 --> 54:53.542
- Well, it's three things.
- Should we bring in an abacus?

54:53.626 --> 54:57.334
All right, let's move to a vote
on both proposals.

54:57.417 --> 55:00.626
All right? First me as... you know,

55:00.709 --> 55:03.126
and Comrade Beria as Vice-Chairman.

55:03.209 --> 55:04.292
All those in favour?

55:08.042 --> 55:09.126
Carried...

55:10.542 --> 55:12.417
u... nanimously.

55:12.501 --> 55:13.501
Right, next.

55:13.626 --> 55:16.084
We need someone
to take charge of the funeral.

55:16.167 --> 55:18.667
- What about Comrade Khrushchev?
- Where's this coming from?

55:18.751 --> 55:20.501
I formally propose Comrade Khrushchev

55:20.584 --> 55:22.384
be given the honour
of organising the funeral.

55:22.459 --> 55:24.227
What? Come on,
I don't have any time to do that.

55:24.251 --> 55:26.435
What if I can do three things at once,
you can at least do two.

55:26.459 --> 55:28.376
What do I know about funerals?

55:28.501 --> 55:30.376
You said you wanted
to honour his legacy.

55:30.459 --> 55:32.501
You told me last night
in the bathroom.

55:35.959 --> 55:38.959
- All those in... all those in favour?
- All those in favour?

55:39.042 --> 55:40.459
No, uh...

55:40.542 --> 55:43.542
Well, I think you'd be good,
actually, you know.

55:46.126 --> 55:47.709
Passed unanimously.

55:47.792 --> 55:50.167
Nicky Khrushchev, funeral director.
It suits you.

55:50.251 --> 55:51.876
- Yeah.
- It suits that face, anyway.

55:54.251 --> 55:57.501
- Comrade Beria.
- I propose a halt to deportations,

55:57.584 --> 56:01.792
the release of some existing detainees
under Article 31 and the suspension

56:01.876 --> 56:04.542
of all arrests that were officially
sanctioned three days ago.

56:04.626 --> 56:09.001
Whoa, whoa. That's like wiping
your arse on Stalin's final list.

56:09.084 --> 56:10.893
- No, no, no.
- This is demonstrably revisionist.

56:10.917 --> 56:15.126
Releasing people we arrested three
days ago will make us look cretinous.

56:15.709 --> 56:17.667
Listen, Stalin was misled.

56:17.792 --> 56:19.917
- We were misled.
- Really?

56:20.001 --> 56:23.126
Yes. So the people responsible
should be found and punished.

56:23.209 --> 56:26.042
Who are you kidding,
Lavrenti, yourself?

56:26.126 --> 56:29.542
We all knew what we were doing
when we signed those lists.

56:29.626 --> 56:35.042
Stalin destroyed the status quo...
and he rebuilt it.

56:36.501 --> 56:37.626
He was liberal.

56:37.751 --> 56:39.167
- Radical.
- He was radical.

56:39.251 --> 56:41.209
This is a blatant attempt
by Comrade Beria

56:41.334 --> 56:42.792
to buy the support of the public.

56:42.876 --> 56:45.796
I thought you were in favour of a more
liberal approach, Comrade Reformer.

56:45.876 --> 56:49.001
All those in favour
of pausing the arrests,

56:49.084 --> 56:51.667
of pausing the executions?

56:53.084 --> 56:54.167
All those in favour?

56:56.376 --> 57:02.084
Hmm. I've always been loyal to Stalin.
Always.

57:02.667 --> 57:05.334
And these arrests
were authorised by Stalin.

57:05.459 --> 57:08.084
But Stalin was also loyal
to the collective leadership,

57:08.167 --> 57:10.542
and that is true loyalty.

57:12.417 --> 57:16.334
However, he also had an iron will,
undeviating, strong.

57:16.417 --> 57:19.251
Should we not do the same
and stick to what we believed in?

57:21.084 --> 57:22.084
No.

57:23.001 --> 57:25.834
It is stronger still
to forge our own beliefs

57:25.917 --> 57:28.876
with the beliefs
of the collective leadership.

57:29.709 --> 57:32.542
